<db:section xml:id="details">
<db:title>Detailed Description</db:title>
<db:para><db:link xlink:href="q3dlight-qtdatavis.xml">Q3DLight</db:link> represents a monochrome light source in 3D space.</db:para>
<db:note>
<db:para>Default light has <db:link xlink:href="q3dlight-qtdatavis.xml#autoPosition-prop">isAutoPosition</db:link>() <db:code>true</db:code>.</db:para>
</db:note>
</db:section>
<db:section xml:id="property-documentation">
<db:title>Property Documentation</db:title>
<db:section xml:id="autoPosition-prop">
<db:title>[since QtDataVisualization 5.9] autoPosition : bool</db:title>
<db:para>This property holds whether the light position follows the camera automatically.</db:para>
<db:note>
<db:para>Has no effect if shadows are enabled. Remember to disable shadows before setting light's position, or it will be overwritten by automatic positioning if <db:code>isAutoPosition()</db:code> is <db:code>false</db:code>.</db:para>
</db:note>
<db:para>This property was introduced in QtDataVisualization 5.9.</db:para>
<db:para>
<db:emphasis role="bold">Access functions:
</db:emphasis>
</db:para>
<db:itemizedlist>
<db:listitem>
<db:para><db:type>bool</db:type> <db:emphasis role="bold">isAutoPosition</db:emphasis>()</db:para>
